# Shared Memory

This project stores persistent memory at `agent_docs/memory/MEMORY.md`.
Both Cursor and Claude Code memory directories are symlinked there — all agents read and write the same files.

## When to update

Update `agent_docs/memory/MEMORY.md` (or its topic files) when you learn:
- A new architectural decision or pattern
- A critical "gotcha" (DB state, build requirement, PATH issue, etc.)
- A customer-facing fact that changed (business_id, credentials location, deployment state)
- A lesson from a mistake that should not be repeated

Do NOT save: in-progress task state, speculative plans, or anything already in git history.

## Topic files

- `agent_docs/memory/customer-onboarding.md` — onboarding playbook for new customers
- `agent_docs/memory/feedback.md` — working style preferences and lessons learned

## Format

Lead with the fact. For feedback/lessons: add a **Why:** line and a **How to apply:** line so future agents understand the context, not just the rule.
